Think about card games you’ve played. What kinds of information do these games require a card object to “know”? 
Card games require that the cards know if they’re the same as another card. 

What kinds of operations do these games require a card object to provide?
The players of the game need to be able to get some information from the card like rank, suit, and point value.

Now think about implementing a class to represent a playing card. What instance variables should it have?
The card class should have a rank, a suit, and a point value. 

What methods should it provide? 
The card should be able to relay information to the players such as its rank, suit, point value, and equality to other cards. 
